@Huawei Huawei’s Tau Scaling brings an interesting shift in the semiconductor conversation.

For decades, chip progress was mainly explained through smaller nodes, higher density, and more transistors. Now the discussion is moving toward time: reducing signal delay, improving data movement, and making chips, memory, software, and systems work together with less friction.

This matters deeply for AI, because faster intelligence will depend on smarter systems, not just faster chips.

